The paper focuses on neural architecture design for class-incremental learning, which is a problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses the CIFAR-100 dataset, which is a popular computer vision dataset, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper uses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of AI, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with neural networks, which is a subfield of both AI and NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with classification tasks, which is a subfield of natural language processing, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
